	{ name: 'The Recombination Hypothesis', number: '13', season_id: '10', description:'Upon arriving home, Sheldon discovers that the cutout of Mr. Spock he ordered is of Zachary Quinto, not Leonard Nimoy. As he gripes about this, Leonard notices Penny across the hall, and spontaneously asks her out on a date. Their dinner starts well, but soon goes sour when Leonard insists on over-analyzing their relationship. He comes home in a bad mood, causing Howard and Raj to assume he and Penny are on the outs. However, that night, Penny invites him over via text, and, after warning him not to talk, they have sex. They agree to keep their relationship secret. When everyone has dinner at the Cheesecake Factory, Leonard overplays his fake annoyance, genuinely angering Penny. They have a late-night argument, followed by more sex. Leonard tells Penny that he cannot imagine this ending well.
The scene shifts back to the hallway, with Sheldon still grousing about Mr. Spock--the whole episode was in Leonard\'s imagination. Nonetheless, he marches into Penny\'s apartment and asks her out. She asks if he\'s thought this over, and he replies that he has, but that they should go anyway. She agrees. The episode ends with Penny imagining herself very pregnant and marrying Leonard, reminding her to stop by the drugstore before the date.
Note: Leonard broke up with Priya prior to "The Good Guy Fluctuation," the seventh episode of the season.
Title reference: Leonard contemplating the ramifications of asking Penny out on a date.', date: '2012-01-19'}, 
	{ name: 'The Beta Test Initiation', number: '14', season_id: '10', description:'Leonard and Penny have started dating again. Anxious to avoid the mistakes of last time, Leonard suggests they have a Alpha test relationship: rather than getting angry with each other, they\'ll simply report any \'bugs\' they discover and fix them. This goes poorly. Leonard gives Penny an insultingly long list of her faults. When he tries to patch things up by taking her target shooting, he accidentally shoots himself in the toe.
Meanwhile, Raj develops a crush on his phone\'s virtual assistant, Siri and Sheldon and Amy start a podcast about the study of flags.
Recurring characters: John Ross Bowie as Barry Kripke Notable guest stars: Becky O\'Donohue as Siri
Title reference: Leonard inventing a system in which Penny and he can communicate their annoyances in the relationship to improve upon it. Penny incorrectly dubs the technique a "beta test" instead of an "alpha test," and Leonard corrects her.', date: '2012-01-26'},
	{ name: 'The Friendship Contraction', number: '15', season_id: '10', description:'Sheldon\'s selfish demands force Leonard to reconsider their friendship. Meanwhile, Howard tries to pick his astronaut nickname.
